Title : Robert Shirley, 6th Earl Ferrers
Text : '''Robert Shirley, 6th Earl Ferrers''' (20 July 1723 – 18 April 1787) was a British nobleman.

He was born in 1723 in [[St James, Westminster]], the third son of Hon. Laurence Shirley.

On 26 December 1754, he married Catherine Cotton (d. 26 March 1786), by whom he had three children:<ref name="stemmata">{{cite book | title=Stemmata Shirleiana | first=Evelyn Philip | last=Shirley | authorlink=Evelyn Shirley (1812–1882) | publisher=Nichols and Sons | location=Westminster | year=1873 | pages=198, 201–202 | url=https://archive.org/details/cu31924029787250}}</ref>
*[[Robert Shirley, 7th Earl Ferrers]] (1756–1824)
*Lawrence Rowland Ferrers (1757 – 5 February 1773), who appears as a youth in [[Joseph Wright of Derby|Joseph Wright]]'s painting, "[[A Philosopher Lecturing on the Orrery]]"
*[[Washington Shirley, 8th Earl Ferrers]] (1760–1842)

In 1778, he succeeded his brother, Vice-Admiral [[Washington Shirley, 5th Earl Ferrers|Ferrers]], in the earldom.<ref name="stemmata" /> On 4 July 1781, he was created a [[deputy lieutenant]] of [[Derbyshire]].<ref name="doyle">{{cite book | last=Doyle | first=James William Edmund | authorlink=James William Edmund Doyle | title=The Official Baronage of England | volume=1 | place=London | publisher=Longmans, Green | year=1886 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=B-kIAAAAIAAJ | page=741}}</ref> He died in his house in [[London]] in 1787 and was buried with his wife at [[Breedon on the Hill]].<ref name="stemmata" />

